reagent-name-atropine = Atropine
reagent-desc-atropine = Plant based chemical replaced and superseded by Epinephrine, it has a plethora of side effects but is considerably stronger than epinephrine.
reagent-name-thymol = Thymol
reagent-desc-thymol = Known chemical used in the 20th century as innovative way to combat hookworm parasites and generally all kinds of infections, it was since used as natural pesticide.
reagent-name-psoralen = Psoralen
reagent-desc-psoralen = Naturally occurring carcinogenic, used commonly as mutagen for DNA research.
reagent-name-coniine = Coniine
